        <p>There are different kinds of variables: (1) basic ones that you create, (2)&#160;custom date/time variables that you create, (3) system variables (e.g., date and time; titles; page count; <MadCap:keyword term="Headers:Chapter Number variables;Footers:chapter number variables;Variables:chapter number variables;Page layouts:Chapter Number variables;Headers:Section Number variables;Headers:Volume Number variables;Footers:section number variables;Footers:Volume Number variables;Page layouts:section number variables;Page layouts:Volume Number variables;Chapters:variables;Sections:variables;Volumes:variables;Variables:section number variables;Variables:volume number variables" />Chapter, Section, and Volume numbers),  (4) <MadCap:keyword MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare" term="Headings:variables;Headers:Heading variables;Footers:heading variables;Variables:heading variables;Page layouts:heading variables;Template pages:Heading variables" />Heading variables, and <MadCap:keyword MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare" term="Template pages:running head variables;Running head variables;Headers:Running Head variables;Footers:running head variables;Variables:running head variables;Page layouts:running head variables" />(5) Running Head variables. Some of these are especially useful for page headers and footers in print-based output.</p>
